evidence\": \"error_ratio p99 increased from 0.0 to 0.56 (200% change), client_error_ratio p99 increased from 0.0 to 0.56 (200% change)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"currencyservice-1\",\n      \"reason\": \"Major latency spike in rrt_max metric affecting service performance\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max p99 increased from 76359.18 to 9218.28 (156.91% change), median rrt_max increased by 14.71%\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"emailservice-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Severe latency degradation in rrt_max metric impacting service responsiveness\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max p99 increased from 9837.6 to 69115.28 (150.16% change), median rrt_max increased by 10.98%\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-04\",\n      \"reason\": \"Node-level memory usage reduction indicating potential resource pressure or cleanup\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_memory_usage_rate decreased from 34.22% to 29.87% (13.56% reduction), p99 decreased by 43.47%\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Analysis Summary\n\nThe fault analysis reveals several key issues:\n\n**Primary Service Issues:**\n1. **adservice-0**: Shows critical error ratio spikes (200% increase) indicating service degradation\n2. **currencyservice-1**: Experienced significant latency spikes (156.91% p99 increase)\n3. **emailservice-0**: Severe latency degradation (150.16% p99 increase)\n\n**Node-Level Observations:**\n- **aiops-k8s-04**: Memory usage reduction suggests potential resource reclamation or cleanup activities\n- **aiops-k8s-06** and **aiops-k8s-08**: Minor filesystem and memory changes, likely secondary effects\n\n**Key Findings:**\n- The fault appears to be primarily service-level rather than infrastructure-level\n- Multiple services show latency degradation, suggesting a cascading effect\n- No significant pod restarts or process changes detected (`pod_processes` stable)\n- Memory and filesystem metrics show minor fluctuations but no critical resource exhaustion\n\nThe most critical issues are the error ratio spikes in adservice-0 and latency degradation in currencyservice-1 and emailservice-0, which likely contributed to the overall system fault."}
